org.apache.abdera2.common.misc
Class PoolManager<T,R>

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.abdera2.common.misc.PoolManager<T,R>
All Implemented Interfaces:
ItemManager<T,R>
public abstract class PoolManager<T,R>
extends Object
implements ItemManager<T,R>

Implements a simple pool manager. By default, an upper limit to the pool is set at 25 entries. New items can always be created, but if more than 25 entries are released back to the pool, extras are discarded. Items added to the stack should never maintain any kind of state as it is entirely possible that different threads will be grabbing items from the pool
